# n8n & Apify Conventions

## Secrets

NEVER commit real secrets. Replace with `YOUR_ACTUAL_*` placeholders:
- `YOUR_ACTUAL_SUPABASE_API_KEY`
- `YOUR_ACTUAL_APIFY_TOKEN`
- `YOUR_ACTUAL_CRM_USERNAME` / `YOUR_ACTUAL_CRM_PASSWORD`
- `YOUR_ACTUAL_SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL`

## Scrape Date Logic

Always adjust to last business day — no Saturday/Sunday dates:

```javascript
const d = new Date();
const day = d.getDay();
if (day === 0) d.setDate(d.getDate() - 2); // Sun → Fri
if (day === 6) d.setDate(d.getDate() - 1); // Sat → Fri
```

## Agent Matching Priority

1. Use stored `crm_agent_id` from `agents` table (direct URL navigation)
2. Fall back to fuzzy matching with `agent_name_aliases` table
3. Require ALL name tokens to appear in CRM dropdown name (strict matching)

## Apify Actor Stability

The DSB CRM loads data via multiple AJAX calls. The scraper must:
1. `waitForFunction` until target spans are populated
2. Read all values → wait 2s → re-read → compare
3. Repeat up to 4 times until values stabilize
4. Use the last stable reading

## n8n Workflow Files

Files in `/n8n` are JSON exports for version control. The live workflows run on `jkdbga.app.n8n.cloud`. When updating:
1. Edit code locally
2. Test in n8n cloud UI
3. Export and save to `/n8n` with secrets replaced
